INTRODUCTION:\par

\pard\ri810\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qc\tx7200\tx9540\fs22 Internet is basically system of interconnected computers through network. But now its use is changing\par
with changing world and it is not just confined to emails or web browsing. Today\rquote s internet also deals with\par
embedded sensors and has led to development of smart homes, smart rural area, e-health care\rquote s etc. and this\par
introduced the concept of IoT [1].\par
Internet of Things refers to interconnection or communication between two or more devices without\par
human-to-human and human-to-computer interaction. Connected devices are equipped with sensors or actuators\par
perceive their surroundings. IOT has four major components which include sensing the device, accessing the\par
device, processing the information of the device, and provides application and services. In addition to this it also\par
provides security and privacy of data [2].\par
Automation has affected every aspect of our daily lives. More improvements are being introduced in\par
almost all fields to reduce human effort and save time. Thinking of the same is trying to introduce automation in\par
the field of track testing. Railroad track is an integral part of any company's asset base, since it provides them\par
with the necessary business functionality. Problems that occur due to problems in railroads need to be\par
overcome. The latest method used by the Indian railroad is the tracking of the train track which requires a lot of\par
manpower and is time-consuming.\par

\pard\ri810\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\tx7200\tx9540\fs28 ABSTRACT:\fs22\par

\pard\ri810\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qc\tx7200\tx9540                   Indian Railways is the largest railway network in Asia and additionally world's second largest network operated\par
underneath a single management. Due to its large size it is difficult to monitor the cracks in tracks manually.\par
This paper deals with this problem and detects cracks in tracks with the help of ultrasonic sensor attached to\par
moving assembly with help of stepper motor. Ultrasonic sensor allows the device to moves back and forth\par
across the track and if there is any fault, it gives information to the cloud server through which railway\par
department is informed on time about cracks and many lives can be saved. This is the application of IoT, due to\par
this it is cost effective system. This effective methodology of continuous observation and assessment of rail\par
tracks might facilitate to stop accidents. This methodology endlessly monitors the rail stress, evaluate the results\par
and provide the rail break alerts such as potential buckling conditions, bending of rails and wheel impact load\par
detection to the concerned authorities.\par
KEYWORDS: IOT, Raspberry, Smart railway, Fault detection.\par

